


Java 16 Features (Interview Important + Examples)

Java 16 introduced several modern language improvements, especially around immutability and pattern matching.

1. Records (Standard Feature) ⭐
.............................................
Records became a permanent feature in Java 16 (not preview anymore).

They are used for immutable data classes (DTOs).

Example
public record Employee(
        int id,
        String name,
        double salary) {
}
Usage
Employee emp =
        new Employee(101, "Sunil", 50000);

System.out.println(emp.id());
System.out.println(emp.name());
System.out.println(emp.salary());
Benefits

✔ No boilerplate code
✔ Immutable object
✔ Auto-generated constructor, getters, equals, hashCode

2. Pattern Matching for instanceof ⭐
..............................................
Simplifies type checking + casting.

Before Java 16
Object obj = "Java";

if (obj instanceof String) {
    String s = (String) obj;
    System.out.println(s);
}
Java 16
Object obj = "Java";

if (obj instanceof String s) {
    System.out.println(s);
}
Benefits

✔ No explicit casting
✔ Cleaner code
✔ Less boilerplate

3. Stream toList() (Improvement preview became popular later)
...............................................
Simplifies collecting streams.

Example
List<String> list =
        List.of("A", "B", "C");

List<String> result =
        list.stream()
            .map(String::toLowerCase)
            .toList();

System.out.println(result);
Output
[a, b, c]
Benefits

✔ No need for Collectors.toList()
✔ More readable

4. Strong Encapsulation of JDK Internals ⭐
....................................................
Java 16 strongly encapsulated internal APIs.

Before
Access to internal JDK APIs was possible
After Java 16
Internal APIs are strongly encapsulated
Benefits

✔ Better security
✔ More stable JDK

5. Unix-Domain Socket Channel Support
..................................
Improves high-performance communication between processes.

Use Case
Microservices communication on same machine
Database connections
High-performance local IPC
6. Packaging Tool (jpackage preview)
..................................................
Used to create native installers.

Example
jpackage --name MyApp --input lib --main-jar app.jar
Output
Creates .exe / .msi / .dmg installers
Real-Time Example (Spring Boot DTO)
Record used as Response DTO
public record CustomerDTO(
        Long id,
        String name,
        String city) {
}
Controller
@GetMapping("/customer")
public CustomerDTO getCustomer() {

    return new CustomerDTO(
            1L,
            "Sunil",
            "Hyderabad");
}
JSON Output
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Sunil",
  "city": "Hyderabad"
}
Interview Summary
Feature	Description
Records	Immutable DTOs (finalized)
Pattern Matching instanceof	No casting needed
Stream toList()	Cleaner collections
Strong Encapsulation	Secure JDK internals
jpackage	Native app packaging
Unix Socket Channels	High-performance IPC


